"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-05-aussie-olympians-slam-farcical-egg-spoon-event-paris-2024-21362287\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The mixed 4\\u00d7100m medley relay has been labelled 'farcical' and 'the egg-and-spoon race of theOlympic Games' by a former Australian Olympian, despite the country claiming bronze in the event.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 23, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7424234861358744e-35, \"text\": \"medley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\"}, {\"begin\": 120, \"end\": 130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999966901400719, \"rank\": 3.3098351587443365e-06, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 131, \"end\": 139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.6392285563760232, \"rank\": 0.5643856802476419, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mixed event came into the Games for the first time in Tokyo, becoming the first ever mixed-gender swimming contest at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 192, \"to\": 327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 250, \"end\": 255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9769608095705549, \"rank\": 0.023582483063713296, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB won the gold inJapan, with USA claiming first prize in Paris, ahead ofChinain silver and the Aussies in bronze place.\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999997683062, \"rank\": 2.2946022389101149e-10, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 364, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999011157857831, \"rank\": 9.809009100211308e-05, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999799911, \"rank\": 1.9932693316830208e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, three-time Olympic medallist forAustraliaJames Magnussen is no fan of the event, questioning whether it should be in the Games at all.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 659, \"end\": 672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I would call it the egg-and-spoon race of theOlympic Games.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is farcical,' Magnussen said on the Matty and the Missile inParispodcast.\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'We have got men swimming against women.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaylee McKeown won the gold medal in the 100m backstroke, she goes up againstRyan Murphy, who got bronze in the men's 100m backstroke.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is about a 15m difference.\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'On their own, they are both amazing products \\u2026 I do not know why we'd want to compare male athletes and female athletes.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then the race itself just ends up this absolute jungle, where one person's ten metres ahead, then the other team switches.\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have got male breaststrokers vs female breaststrokers.\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's just a shambles of an event.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not understand why it's at the Olympic Games, and I can not understand giving out Olympic medals to that event.\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'You are telling me at the end of the day that that's worth the same as individual gold for Ariarne Titmus in the 400m freestyle?\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1578, \"end\": 1592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not comparable.'\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aussie legend Stephanie Rice won three golds in the pool at Beijing 2008 and she too has doubts about the mixed event.\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Rice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephanie Rice\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Rice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Rice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I feel very mixed about it.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like it's a token event.\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the sense that it feels more fun, than a purist race,' she said on Stan Sports' Olympic Daily.\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stan_(service)\", \"score\": 0.9999999450328703, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stan Sports\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stan_(service)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stan_(service)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'But I like that swimming is looking at different ways of evolving.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the same as the men having an 800 metre freestyle and the women having a 1500 metre freestyle.'\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Avoid these easily misunderstood phrases while travelling in France  ArrowMORE:Team GB athlete in 'floods of tears' after terrible Olympic pole vault attempt  ArrowMORE:What does repechage mean at the Paris 2024 Olympics?\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2284, \"end\": 2290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6214920018014163, \"rank\": 0.606773893735508, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How it works  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2765, \"end\": 2771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"score\": 0.6784377202962604, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punchy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 3008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3069, \"entities\": []}]}"